<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!--
  Sample XML dataset: City Transit Network
  =========================================
  CYCLIC graph – metro stations reference each other bidirectionally.
  The ``reference`` attribute uses XPath to link back to already-defined
  station nodes, creating cycles in the resulting graph.

  Mapping:
    <station>        → node
    <line>           → node  (intermediate grouping)
    <connection>     → edge via ``reference`` attribute (cyclic back-reference)
    text leaf elems  → attributes on the parent node
-->
